     {q:"Why might a tragic hero’s downfall create a powerful emotional impact for readers?", options:["A character with no flaws creates a more powerful impact","Downfalls have no emotional effect on readers","Readers may sympathize with a character who has both strengths and flaws","Tragic heroes never earn any sympathy from readers"], answer:2},
     {q:"Which is an example of a possible tragic flaw?", options:["A trait unrelated to the character’s choices","A strength that always leads to success","A character with no decisions to make","Excessive pride leading to poor decisions"], answer:3},
     {q:"Why is the tragic hero considered an important literary archetype?", options:["It explores the complex relationship between human strengths and weaknesses","This concept has no connection to character development","Tragic heroes never appear in significant works of literature","This archetype has no significance in literature"], answer:0}
