     {q:"Canada’s restrictive immigration policies during this period are now ___.", options:["Viewed as having no lasting impact on historical understanding","Widely studied and critically examined","Considered to have no historical significance","Entirely forgotten with no historical record"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why do historians study Canada’s response to the Holocaust?", options:["This response has no relevance to Canadian history","This topic has no connection to historical study","To understand and reflect on historical decisions and their consequences","Canada had no immigration policy during this era"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might reflecting on past immigration policies be valuable for understanding present-day decisions?", options:["It can offer insight into the impact of policy choices on vulnerable populations","Historical reflection serves no useful purpose","Immigration policy has never changed throughout history","Past policies have no connection to present-day decision-making"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why is Canada’s response to the Holocaust considered an important part of history education?", options:["It has no connection to understanding history","Canada’s role during this period should not be studied","This topic has no educational value","It encourages critical reflection on the consequences of restrictive policies"], answer:3}
