     {q:"Why might legislation like the Employment Equity Act continue to be studied and discussed today?", options:["It reflects ongoing efforts to address workplace equity and inclusion","This legislation has no relevance to modern discussions of workplace rights","Workplace discrimination has never been a historical concern","This topic has no connection to Canadian history"], answer:0}
