     {q:"Why do scientists study plate tectonics when assessing earthquake risk?", options:["Earthquake risk cannot be assessed using any scientific method","Plate tectonics has no connection to earthquake risk","It helps identify regions where stress is likely to build and be released","A reason unrelated to earth science"], answer:2}
