     {q:"Why is the National Energy Program still discussed in relation to Canadian federalism?", options:["A reason unrelated to its historical significance","It resolved all regional tensions in Canada permanently","It illustrates ongoing tensions between regional interests and federal policy","It has no connection to understanding Canadian federalism"], answer:2}
